./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1544:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:13:2. **Self-quotation.** When the composer plays a phrase that scored high on arc payoff, low on click count, and matched intended mood, that phrase is sampled back from `SuperCollider:out_1` and stored under `samples/self/`. Next session, transformed fragments of that phrase return as melodic memory — the Eno tape-loop / Reich phasing aesthetic. The music remembers itself.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1546:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:20:2. **Memory-tagged, mood-aware selection.** Samples carry rich metadata. The sample-selector matches samples to current artist mode, arc phase, harmonic context, and mood — never random. A sample picked for *Solitary* mode will never appear in *Working ambience* mode unless the metadata aligns.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1547:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:38:- Loudness-matching or mastering of stored samples. Per-sample gain is part of the metadata; the mix engine handles overall balance.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1548:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:42:**Phase 1 — Foundations (CCS-001..CCS-008).** Sample data model, on-disk library layout, tag taxonomy, mood/mode-aware selector, character-registry entry for `voice_sampler`, signature-voice quintet update. Pure Python + tests. At end of phase, the selector picks plausible samples for any (mode, arc, mood) tuple from a library of stub/placeholder files; no audio plays yet.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1550:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:46:**Phase 3 — Live capture daemon (CCS-015..CCS-021).** `sample_capture_daemon.py` maintains rolling 60-second buffers of contact mic + room mic via JACK input; an interesting-moment detector flags acoustically novel windows; flagged windows get saved to `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` with auto-generated tags (arc phase, mood, time, who-is-in-room, acoustic features); systemd unit keeps the daemon running. End of phase: leaving the daemon running for an hour produces ~10–30 tagged WAV files representing the room's acoustic life.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1551:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:48:**Phase 4 — Composer integration (CCS-022..CCS-028).** Mode-driven sampler density (solitary heavy, working light, etc.); `select_sample()` wired into cast/instrument-patch path so the composer treats the sampler as a first-class voice; self-quotation loop captures composer output when arc-payoff is high; keyboard/Theramini capture during human play; per-mode effects-bus presets; operator diagnostics surface currently-active samples. End of phase: pieces start to noticeably *cite themselves* across sessions, and the room's acoustic history becomes audible material.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1554:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:77:  - `library/` — handpicked curated samples (committed metadata only, audio files large)
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1555:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:91:| CCS-003 | Implement `SampleLibrary` on-disk store backed by `index.sqlite` with tag/source/pitch/mood-range queries. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleLibrary(root: Path)` opens / creates `index.sqlite` with table `samples` carrying every `SampleRecord` field plus full-text-search index on `character_tags`<br/>- `library.add(record)` persists row + verifies file presence<br/>- `library.find(source=, character_any=, character_all=, pitch_band=, arc_phase=, mood_range=, limit=)` returns ordered list (most recent first within match set)<br/>- tests cover insert, query by each filter, empty-result path, and corrupted-DB rebuild |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1557:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:93:| CCS-005 | Implement `SampleSelector` mood/mode/arc-aware picker with deterministic seed-based selection within match set. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleSelector(library, rng_seed: int)` exposes `select(mode: ArtistMode, arc_phase: str, mood: Mapping[str,float], target_character: tuple[str,...] = (), avoid_recent: int = 5) -> SampleRecord \| None`<br/>- selection prefers samples with matching `arc_phase` and overlapping mood (dot-product over energy/valence/arousal); falls back to character_tags only; falls back to library random within source-source preference per-mode<br/>- `avoid_recent` excludes the N most-recently-played samples (per-mode rolling window)<br/>- per-mode source preference: solitary→[self,contact,room,library]; companion→[library,self,room]; working_ambience→[room,library]; evening_reflection→[self,library,theramini]; storm→[contact,library,room]<br/>- selection is deterministic given (library state, rng_seed, kwargs)<br/>- tests verify per-mode preference order, mood-overlap ranking, avoid_recent, deterministic replay |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1558:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:102:| CCS-014 | Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. | MUST | T1 | - `master_bus.apply_master_bus_scene` recognizes a `sampler_bus` mix slot with default gain -3 dB (peak-normalized so quieter library samples don't disappear)<br/>- post-mix compression for the sampler slot has `compression_ratio = 1.5` (lower than the 4.0 used elsewhere) so grain transients survive<br/>- tests verify gain staging on a known-amplitude input and grain-transient preservation via peak-vs-RMS ratio |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1559:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:105:| CCS-017 | Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → "warm"; narrow-band high-centroid → "metallic"; sustained_amplitude_ratio>0.7 → "sustained"; transient_density>3/sec → "percussive"; pitch_confidence>0.7 → "harmonic"; etc.<br/>- tests verify each heuristic against canned fixtures and that the merged record validates against `SampleRecord` schema |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1560:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:106:| CCS-018 | Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::save_capture(window, source, tags) -> SampleRecord` writes WAV with filename pattern `<source>_<YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ>_<arc>_<sampleid>.wav`<br/>- WAV is 24-bit PCM, 48 kHz, peak-normalized to -1 dBFS unless `peak < -30 dBFS` in which case raw is preserved<br/>- record inserted into `index.sqlite` with `gain_db` set to the normalization adjustment<br/>- tests verify file presence, format (24/48), peak-normalize behavior, and DB row |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1561:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:107:| CCS-019 | Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` post-song hook calls `sample_capture_daemon::self_quote(score_summary)` when arc_payoff > 0.6 AND click_count == 0 AND mode != working_ambience<br/>- daemon captures from `SuperCollider:out_1` (via `system:capture_X` after a small JACK loopback connection it manages itself) the 4-second window centered on the moment of peak rolling_peak during the song<br/>- saves to `samples/self/` with `arc_phase`, `mood`, `mode`, and a `self_quote_source_song_id` extra tag<br/>- tests with a mock self-listener stream and arc-payoff fixture verify trigger condition, capture window, and tag propagation |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1563:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:116:| CCS-028 | Composer post-piece hook: write a sample-usage journal entry per piece (which samples played, what transformations, what arc payoff). | MUST | T1 | - `samples/usage_journal.jsonl` appended one line per piece with `piece_id`, `started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used: list[{sample_id, source, transposition, fx_preset, played_at_row}]`, `arc_payoff`, `clicks`<br/>- journal is durable (fsynced after each line)<br/>- tests verify schema and atomicity |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1564:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:120:| CCS-032 | Migrate Anthony's existing recorded music + handpicked field recordings into `samples/library/` with appropriate metadata. | SHOULD | T2 | - `tools/sample_library_import.py` script reads a TOML manifest of source files + intended tags and inserts them into the library<br/>- supports both single-file and directory imports<br/>- preserves provenance (original path, captured-by) in `SampleRecord` extras<br/>- 100+ samples land in the library with accurate tags<br/>- tests cover the importer with a small fixture manifest |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1565:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:131:The piece's sample-usage journal entry shows all three samples, their transformations, and the arc-payoff. The face/inkplate display showed "♫ sampling room" during the piece, then "♫ memory: self/<song_id>" when the self-quotation played. The metrics-CI gate reports `sampler_event_count = 3`, `sampler_dominating = false`, and `sampler_silent_quintet_member = false`.
