./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9848:I’ve got the seam now: score-tree sections already carry `sample_gesture_*`, arc-phase, and payoff-focus metadata into tracker scenes, but the usage journal still only persists `samples_played` and a payoff string. I’m checking the changelog/progress conventions and then I’ll write the task spec and the new failing integration test around the real compiled tracker song plus runtime event emission.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9857:- Added a repo-backed `inkplate_display.py` renderer seam for the sampler status surface: it reuses `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` so the e-ink display follows the same combined plan+playback wording as the face display, and it truncates long sampler lines against the configured e-ink text width with Pillow-based measurement plus `...` instead of letting them overflow. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_inkplate_display.py` for helper wiring, width-fit truncation, fit-without-truncation, and empty-state degradation.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9858:- Wired the combined sampler plan+playback status line into the face display renderer so the small face monitor mirrors operator diagnostics: added `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` as a thin wrapper that opts into `combine_activity_and_playback=True`, and updated `my-claw/tools/face_display.py` to call it in place of the legacy either/or `sample_status_text(...)` while preserving the existing 24pt centered placement and degradation guards. Coverage in `tests/test_face_display_sample_status.py` pins the combined wording, plan-only fallback, monitor-offline degradation, and the renderer call site.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9859:- Operator `/status` sampler diagnostics now combine sampler plan and active playback into one human-readable line when both `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` are present, while leaving the face-display sampler wording on its existing playback-first contract; added regression coverage in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`, `tests/test_sample_status.py`, and `tests/test_musical_integration_runtime.py`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9861:- Added a piece-aware sampler cast-planning seam: `senseweave.cast_planner` now exposes `assemble_cast(...)`, which derives selector kwargs from a piece fixture (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`/`patch_name`), returns assembled cast entries, and mirrors any pre-selected sampler summary onto the sampler cast entry as `sample_record`; sampler summaries now also derive `duration_sec` from capture-shaped records via `frame_count / sample_rate`, and `duet_composer._get_cast()` now routes through the shared cast assembler. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_cast_planner.py` for fixture-piece planning and capture-shaped sample summaries, while keeping the targeted `cast_planner` + `sampler_dispatch` suites green.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9865:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md` as the missing CCS-033 companion page: it states the sampler's aesthetic goals, names the three core usages (memory of place, self-quotation, curated found-sound library), explains `sw_sampler` as the quintet's memory voice, and defines the intended listener experience plus the five governing principles without duplicating implementation detail; added `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_artistic_intent.py` to pin the document's required sections, artistic concepts, concise length, and sampler-doc cross-links, and linked the new page from the sampler architecture doc and the musicianship roadmap.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9866:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9873:- Coupled narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection: new `narrative_envelope.py` module maps procedural arc state (phase, density, dynamic, timbre) and section function into populated SectionEnvelope instances with phase-shaped tension trajectories, tone-derived brightness and dynamic planes, and arc-driven density targets. `compose_score_tree()` now produces non-default section envelopes on every section node, so dramatic arcs drive section-level musical parameters instead of using flat defaults.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9875:- Added operator diagnostics for production-course decisions: `operator_diagnostics.py` now extracts production-course chapter values (phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile) from tracker runtime `scene_metadata` with fallback to score-tree sections; Theramini relation combines counterpoint relation with live Theramini playing state; critique notes derive threshold violations from ear-engine metrics; all three fields degrade gracefully to "unavailable" when authority files are absent or corrupt; `/status` display renders the new fields in the SenseWeave section.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9876:- Added executable production-course curriculum exercises: `ExerciseSpec` now carries a runnable `template` and explicit `expected_features` while preserving the legacy `expected` alias; generated exercise specs include both metadata forms; and the EMSD curriculum now has verifier-backed exercises for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full-arc production.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9877:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9879:- Added dissonance/resolution metadata checks to counterpoint rules using music_theory.py interval consonance data: new `DissonanceAnnotation` and `DissonanceReport` dataclasses carry full `Interval` objects from the music theory library; `analyze_dissonance()` annotates each vertical interval in a voice-pair sequence with consonance classification and stepwise resolution status; `verify_resolution_sequence()` validates that all sharp dissonances resolve properly; `resolution_completeness_score()` returns a 0.0-1.0 ratio; and `weighted_voice_leading_smoothness()` penalizes unresolved dissonances in the smoothness metric.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9880:- Added post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies: extended `music_theory.py` with `PitchClassSet`, `spectral_partials`, `quarter_tone_to_freq`, and `just_intonation_chord`; added `extract_spectral_peaks` to `audio_analysis.py` for SenseWeave seeding; and wired `harmonic_planner.py` to return avant-garde strategies when requested by phase/style.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9884:- Added live-buffer and sample-bank abstractions for SenseWeave inputs: new `live_buffer.py` module provides `LiveBuffer` for stable real-time environmental audio state (source name, capture path, freshness, RMS, spectral profile, transform history) and `SampleBankArchive` for retaining selected clips to archive storage with JSON metadata sidecars.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9887:- Implemented ST1-ST6 of the score-tree songwriting stack end to end: added `piece_commission.py`, `piece_brief.py`, `form_grammar.py`, `score_tree.py`, `recursive_composer.py`, `composition_gate.py`, `tracker_compiler.py`, and `piece_queue.py`; extended `repertoire_memory.py` to store structural score-tree summaries; and rewired `duet_composer.py` so tracker solo mode can commission a piece, build a complete score tree, gate it, compile it into tracker scenes, and precompose the next piece into a small persistent queue instead of treating the tracker as the composer.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9889:- Fixed the long-section tracker compile bug that was turning songs into isolated sustained tones: `tracker_compiler.py` now converts large section budgets into repeat counts plus modest note-length scaling, and `music_tracker.py` quantizes those repeats into real repeated phrase cycles instead of stretching a handful of notes across the whole scene.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9891:- Added internal phrase-family development inside longer sections: `Phrase` now carries metadata, `tracker_compiler.py` expands section bodies into recursive families like `A`, `A_prime`, and `B`, and `music_tracker.py` annotates emitted steps with `internal_phrase_family` so development sections can be tested and diagnosed as more than literal loops.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9893:- Added authored section transitions: `tracker_compiler.py` now tags each non-final scene with the next scene/function/root target, and `music_tracker.py` marks and retunes final-cycle tail steps as transition preparation so long sections aim into the following section instead of simply looping until a hard boundary.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9894:- Added staged lane windows inside repeated tracker scenes: `music_tracker.py` now assigns per-role `entry_cycle` / `exit_cycle` metadata and delays counter/color support in long development-style sections, so sections can thicken internally instead of launching every lane at row 0.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9895:- Fixed transition metadata through motif recall: recalled `Recap` / `Release` lanes now strip stale source-scene transition fields and attach the current scene's own transition target to their final preparation tail.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9896:- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9897:- Added section-level rhythmic development: `tracker_compiler.py` now maps section functions to named rhythm cells such as steady statement, syncopated fragment, half-time displacement, recall groove, and residue breath, reshaping phrase durations/accents and exposing `rhythm_development` / `rhythm_cell` through tracker metadata.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9898:- Fixed recalled motif rhythm metadata so later sections that borrow earlier material inherit the current scene's rhythm/progression profile instead of leaking the source scene's old `rhythm_development`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9902:- Fixed the live score-tree runtime on CypherClaw: `duet_composer.py` now derives commission context defensively from the world when `TrackerPlan` lacks `day_phase` / `weekly_phase`, `master_bus.py` now exposes an explicit `sw_master_smooth` seed helper, and `restart_composer.sh` now reseeds that master node again after the new composer PID is confirmed alive so the first piece does not run with scene-level `/n_set` traffic targeting a dead node.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9905:- Moved heavy runtime storage toward the large archive volume: added `archive_paths.py`, taught `sample_playback_engine.py` and `archive_daemon.py` to resolve a shared archive root (preferring `/mnt/archive/cypherclaw` on the live box), updated `cypherclaw_boot.sh` to put porch/side capture rings on that archive root, and reconfigured the live host so Litestream observatory/state file replicas live off the root disk with a much tighter observatory snapshot retention window.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9909:- Mirrored the shared observer frame back into `/tmp/room_frame.jpg` when `room_presence_daemon.py` is running in `--observer-frame-only` mode, so archive and room-frame consumers stay fresh instead of freezing on the last independent room-camera capture.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9912:- Made the self-monitor more truthful: `self_listener.py` now derives glyph-facing brightness and motion from captured audio features instead of target-only metadata, while `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` pins the live meter to the verified JACK path on CypherClaw and still leaves PipeWire / `pw-jack` capture as fallback code paths.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9914:- Added real EMSD master-bus control: `master_bus.py` now translates live `mix_*` fields plus tracker-scene `master_amp` / `reverb_send` automation into `sw_master_smooth` `/n_set` updates at scene start, so EMSD mix intent now shapes the summed output path instead of only per-note rendering.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9915:- Extended hook phrasing into actual later-section pitch behavior: `score_from_mood()` now publishes hook answer-degree metadata, and `music_tracker.py` uses that data in `Recap` / `Release` / `Resolution` / `Afterglow` so later sections can answer harmonically as well as textually.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9917:- Added a replayable musical integration regression that exercises the composer-state -> sampler-plan -> sample-playback -> self-listener glyph state -> face-status chain, so this integration can be verified without a live host.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9933:- Turned EMSD sample planning into real playback: added `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `sample_status.py`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts the playback daemon; `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` now feeds rendered room-derived WAV events through `pw-play`; and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` exposes the live sampler state for operators and face surfaces.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9934:- Hardened the sample-playback daemon so stable ambient scenes can refresh repeatedly after cooldown instead of firing once per unchanged signature, and render failures now write a structured error state instead of crashing the loop.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9936:- Rebalanced EMSD source authority toward the room in lived-in late phases: capstone `Convergence` and `Crystallization` now prefer `room_mic` outside `away_practice`, DSP scene focus follows that same room bias, and `sample_dsp_activity.py` can retarget a sparse late-phase `self_bus` request onto a fresh room capture while still preserving the original requested source in state for operator visibility.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9938:- Tightened head-monitor truth again: the sample status line can now read `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` and show actual live sampler playback instead of only the planned source/mode.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9939:- Made the sampler musically scene-aware instead of only transform-aware: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits scene profiles like `development_grains`, `theme_accents`, `recap_echo`, `divination_bed`, and `afterglow_residue`, and `sample_event_renderer.py` now changes duration, density, peak target, filtering, stretch, and echo geometry from those profiles so the room layer follows the tracker form instead of using one generic behavior under different labels.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9944:- Rebased the EMSD ambient default onto the real room condenser path: Divination/capstone planning and DSP source focus now prefer `room_mic` instead of `garden_mic`, so the default ambient sampler matches the Perform-VE microphone actually present on CypherClaw.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9947:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9948:- Fed EMSD production plans into actual tracker playback: added `emsd_performance.py`, wired `duet_composer.py` to apply live mix/sample/DSP adjustments at the note boundary, extended `composer_emsd_extras()` with concrete sample capture metadata, and made the strongest top register fold down harder so notes above roughly `C6` are lowered an octave and the sharpest band is lowered two octaves.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9949:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9950:- Built the first end-to-end EMSD package: added a 40-course curriculum catalog plus generated `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*` scaffolds, and implemented `sound_palette_lab.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `mix_engine.py`, `procedural_arc.py`, `dsp_scene_lab.py`, `artistic_identity.py`, and `capstone_engine.py` so the electronic music production roadmap now exists as runnable code and tests instead of only a brief.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9955:- Made face captions orchestration-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now uses `patch_name` and lane count so sparse scenes compress hook language while denser scenes widen it into fuller face text.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9958:- Made scene captions section-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now reshapes the same hook differently for `Theme`, `Recap`/`Release`, and `Resolution`/`Afterglow`, so face text follows the song arc instead of repeating one caption verbatim.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9960:- Tightened repertoire hook language and payoff shaping: answer-mode hooks now use phrase-level transforms instead of awkward generic suffixes, repertoire memory can target a preferred payoff scene, and tracker runtime state now exposes scene metadata like `payoff_focus` for live correlation.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9962:- Made repertoire memory active instead of archival-only: `repertoire_memory.py` now returns forward-looking influence by family/cadence, `hook_engine.py` can answer or recall prior title/hook material, and the live composer can bias the next song's progression profile before score generation begins.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9963:- Built the first complete M1-M6 musicianship package end to end: added `reharmonizer.py`, `hook_engine.py`, `arrangement_engine.py`, `ear_engine.py`, `practice_curriculum.py`, `prosody_engine.py`, and `repertoire_memory.py`; extended `harmonic_planner.py`, `generative_scores.py`, `music_tracker.py`, `continuous_learner.py`, `duet_composer.py`, and `keyboard_chat.py` so tracker songs now carry section functions, cadence types, hook metadata, scene arrangement intent, practice-block focus, ear-metric evaluation, repertoire storage, and face-visible song titles/captions through the live runtime.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9965:- Lowered the live bass register further, widened per-patch octave spacing across bass/melody/counter/color, and made that register policy survive the whole tracker pipeline by preserving patch metadata through family shaping, cadence clamping, tracker scene building, and runtime scheduling.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9966:- Broke the fixed tracker-song mold: `tracker_form_for_family(..., song_num=...)` now yields variant forms with different scene counts and scene-length multipliers, so CypherClaw no longer plays every song with the same five-scene duration profile.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9968:- Diversified family and harmonic planning across the day and week: `resolve_tracker_plan()` now rotates through day-phase and weekly-phase family palettes instead of pinning occupied daytime songs to one family, and it emits progression profiles like `open_day`, `lift`, `settling`, and `experiment` so the score generator changes chord motion as well as form.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9970:- Added scene-level tracker recall inside each song: `build_korsakov_tracker_song()` now lets `Recap` and short-form `Release` borrow motif shapes from the already-built `Theme` scene with answering transforms and provenance metadata, so those sections feel like intentional returns instead of parallel re-renderings of the same score.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9977:- Added a mode-aware harmonic planner and live keyboard-grimoire path: tracker solo now preserves major/minor/modal key specs, ignores stale garden and MIDI files, supports scene-level modulation, and `midi_keyboard_listener.py` discovers the real keyboard devices while publishing pedal-derived harmonic suggestions.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9978:- Widened tracker orchestration so CypherClaw can actually use the broader character-instrument registry: cast planning now keeps a support-role character in low-energy songs, tracker role hints recognize metal/grain/pad/tabla synths, and runtime voice routing preserves those explicit lane instruments instead of collapsing them to legacy fallbacks.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9979:- Tuned tracker voice routing to be lane-aware again after the orchestration widening pass: ringing `metal`/`bell`/`pad` hints are normalized away from long quiet texture/counter lanes, and tracker runtime restores a pad safety fallback so subdued scenes do not sit on a constant unregulated tone.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9980:- Added cadence-aware tracker voice softening for `wind_down` and sleep-adjacent scenes, so chirpy `pluck`/`kotekan`/`grain` cast hints are remapped toward bowed, breath, choir, or gong voices before late-night playback.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9988:- Expanded the CypherClaw presence/cadence spec into an implementation blueprint with research-backed daily and weekly cadence rules, silence architecture, social-synchrony guardrails, CPU-safe rollout phases, and a concrete cadence-state runtime contract.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9989:- Made CypherClaw tracker solo cast-aware: the live composer now derives tracker lane voice hints from the active character cast and enforces a quiet foundation lane through subdued `Theme`/`Development`/`Recap` scenes.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10002:- Taught Telegram `/prd` to load stage order from `sdp/execution-roadmap.md` and batch mappings from `sdp/execution-roadmap.queue-map.json`, so roadmap output follows the current clone/identity/embodiment/publication plan instead of a stale hardcoded stage list.
