./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:11670:| CCS-022 | Wire `SampleSelector` into `cast_planner.select_cast_ids` so when the cast includes `sw_sampler`, a sample is pre-selected for the piece and attached to the cast metadata. | MUST | T1 | - `select_cast_ids` (or a sibling `assemble_cast`) returns cast entries with optional `sample_record: SampleRecord` field for sampler voices<br/>- selection happens once per piece commission and passes mode + arc_phase + mood + target_character (drawn from `instrument_patches.select_instrument_patch`)<br/>- tests verify sampler voices in cast carry a sample_record and that the record matches selector contracts |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:11673:| CCS-025 | Sample-aware harmonic planning: when a sample with known `pitch_hz` is selected, transpose to fit the current piece's key by computing the closest in-key root and applying `pitch_transpose_semitones`. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch::transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> semitones` returns the integer transposition that maps `record.pitch_hz` to the nearest pitch in the current key (B-rooted modes preferred)<br/>- when `record.pitch_confidence < 0.4`, transposition is set to 0 and the sample plays "atonally" as a texture<br/>- tests verify transposition for known pitch + key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and edge cases (octave wraps) |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:11676:| CCS-028 | Composer post-piece hook: write a sample-usage journal entry per piece (which samples played, what transformations, what arc payoff). | MUST | T1 | - `samples/usage_journal.jsonl` appended one line per piece with `piece_id`, `started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used: list[{sample_id, source, transposition, fx_preset, played_at_row}]`, `arc_payoff`, `clicks`<br/>- journal is durable (fsynced after each line)<br/>- tests verify schema and atomicity |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:11679:| CCS-031 | End-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw: capture a known room sound, watch the composer self-quote it within 3 pieces, verify the self-listener observes the resulting peaks. | MUST | T1 | - `my-claw/tests/test_sampler_e2e.py` (skipped on CI, runs on cypherclaw via `pytest -m cypherclaw_e2e`)<br/>- plays a 4-second sine sweep through the speakers, lets contact/room mic capture it, waits for the daemon to detect+tag, forces the composer to compose 3 short pieces, asserts at least one of them dispatched a sampler with the captured sample<br/>- self-listener observes nonzero peak in the expected scene<br/>- documented in `docs/sampler-smoke-test.md` |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:11680:| CCS-032 | Migrate Anthony's existing recorded music + handpicked field recordings into `samples/library/` with appropriate metadata. | SHOULD | T2 | - `tools/sample_library_import.py` script reads a TOML manifest of source files + intended tags and inserts them into the library<br/>- supports both single-file and directory imports<br/>- preserves provenance (original path, captured-by) in `SampleRecord` extras<br/>- 100+ samples land in the library with accurate tags<br/>- tests cover the importer with a small fixture manifest |
