./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:25997:- Added a repo-backed `inkplate_display.py` renderer seam for the sampler status surface: it reuses `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` so the e-ink display follows the same combined plan+playback wording as the face display, and it truncates long sampler lines against the configured e-ink text width with Pillow-based measurement plus `...` instead of letting them overflow. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_inkplate_display.py` for helper wiring, width-fit truncation, fit-without-truncation, and empty-state degradation.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:25998:- Wired the combined sampler plan+playback status line into the face display renderer so the small face monitor mirrors operator diagnostics: added `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` as a thin wrapper that opts into `combine_activity_and_playback=True`, and updated `my-claw/tools/face_display.py` to call it in place of the legacy either/or `sample_status_text(...)` while preserving the existing 24pt centered placement and degradation guards. Coverage in `tests/test_face_display_sample_status.py` pins the combined wording, plan-only fallback, monitor-offline degradation, and the renderer call site.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:25999:- Operator `/status` sampler diagnostics now combine sampler plan and active playback into one human-readable line when both `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` are present, while leaving the face-display sampler wording on its existing playback-first contract; added regression coverage in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`, `tests/test_sample_status.py`, and `tests/test_musical_integration_runtime.py`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26001:- Added a piece-aware sampler cast-planning seam: `senseweave.cast_planner` now exposes `assemble_cast(...)`, which derives selector kwargs from a piece fixture (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`/`patch_name`), returns assembled cast entries, and mirrors any pre-selected sampler summary onto the sampler cast entry as `sample_record`; sampler summaries now also derive `duration_sec` from capture-shaped records via `frame_count / sample_rate`, and `duet_composer._get_cast()` now routes through the shared cast assembler. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_cast_planner.py` for fixture-piece planning and capture-shaped sample summaries, while keeping the targeted `cast_planner` + `sampler_dispatch` suites green.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26005:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md` as the missing CCS-033 companion page: it states the sampler's aesthetic goals, names the three core usages (memory of place, self-quotation, curated found-sound library), explains `sw_sampler` as the quintet's memory voice, and defines the intended listener experience plus the five governing principles without duplicating implementation detail; added `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_artistic_intent.py` to pin the document's required sections, artistic concepts, concise length, and sampler-doc cross-links, and linked the new page from the sampler architecture doc and the musicianship roadmap.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26006:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26013:- Coupled narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection: new `narrative_envelope.py` module maps procedural arc state (phase, density, dynamic, timbre) and section function into populated SectionEnvelope instances with phase-shaped tension trajectories, tone-derived brightness and dynamic planes, and arc-driven density targets. `compose_score_tree()` now produces non-default section envelopes on every section node, so dramatic arcs drive section-level musical parameters instead of using flat defaults.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26015:- Added operator diagnostics for production-course decisions: `operator_diagnostics.py` now extracts production-course chapter values (phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile) from tracker runtime `scene_metadata` with fallback to score-tree sections; Theramini relation combines counterpoint relation with live Theramini playing state; critique notes derive threshold violations from ear-engine metrics; all three fields degrade gracefully to "unavailable" when authority files are absent or corrupt; `/status` display renders the new fields in the SenseWeave section.
