./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:29602:+- Added the missing CCS-028 sample-usage journal seam for tracker pieces: `senseweave.usage_journal` now serializes the richer per-piece sampler fields (`started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used`, `transformations`, `clicks`) while preserving the legacy `timestamp` / `samples_played` aliases, `music_tracker_runtime.ScheduledTrackerEvent` now carries sample-gesture metadata through playback emission, `duet_composer.py` now records actual emitted sample-lane events into the post-piece journal hook, and new regression coverage in `tests/test_usage_journal.py`, `tests/test_music_tracker_runtime.py`, and `tests/test_usage_journal_integration.py` composes a short score-tree piece end to end and proves the written journal entry contains populated sample usage, transformations, and arc payoff data.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:29604: - Added a repo-backed `inkplate_display.py` renderer seam for the sampler status surface: it reuses `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` so the e-ink display follows the same combined plan+playback wording as the face display, and it truncates long sampler lines against the configured e-ink text width with Pillow-based measurement plus `...` instead of letting them overflow. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_inkplate_display.py` for helper wiring, width-fit truncation, fit-without-truncation, and empty-state degradation.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:29605: - Wired the combined sampler plan+playback status line into the face display renderer so the small face monitor mirrors operator diagnostics: added `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` as a thin wrapper that opts into `combine_activity_and_playback=True`, and updated `my-claw/tools/face_display.py` to call it in place of the legacy either/or `sample_status_text(...)` while preserving the existing 24pt centered placement and degradation guards. Coverage in `tests/test_face_display_sample_status.py` pins the combined wording, plan-only fallback, monitor-offline degradation, and the renderer call site.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:29618:+- **Details:** Exploration mapped this subtask to the active score-tree tracker path rather than the older freeform solo path. `tracker_compiler.py` already routes final score selection through `revise_score()`, `music_tracker.py` already projects sample-gesture source/mode/transform metadata into tracker scenes and sample lanes, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` already owns the end-to-end event-emission seam used by playback tests. The missing piece is the post-piece journal contract in `senseweave.usage_journal.py`: it currently persists only `piece_id`, `timestamp`, `samples_played`, and `arc_payoff`, while the sampler PRD (`my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md`, CCS-028) expects a richer per-piece entry including sample usage, transformations, mode, and clicks. This task will extend that journal seam in a backward-compatible way and add a real compose → gate → compile → schedule → journal regression test rather than inventing a new playback pipeline. No new dependencies or migrations are required. `progress.md` is generated and already dirty, so the exploration update there is limited to the single `T-022@20260425T183959Zd` task line. The recurring hardening anchors about `revise_score()` wiring, resource-governor budget enforcement, and startup identity sequencing will be re-run during verification, but only the journal/track-runtime area is in scope for code changes here.
