./sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:30501: - Added a repo-backed `inkplate_display.py` renderer seam for the sampler status surface: it reuses `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` so the e-ink display follows the same combined plan+playback wording as the face display, and it truncates long sampler lines against the configured e-ink text width with Pillow-based measurement plus `...` instead of letting them overflow. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_inkplate_display.py` for helper wiring, width-fit truncation, fit-without-truncation, and empty-state degradation.
