y checks.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Update CHANGELOG.md, progress.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- No questions — document assumptions in ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do not modify locked test assertions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Log new dependencies to ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Commit per sub-task: `feat(scope): summary [T-022@20260416T054258Z]`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Common Pitfalls (from recurring verify feedback)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThese are the top reasons tasks get PASS WITH NOTES instead of clean PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAvoid them on the first attempt:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Always include a migration** when adding or modifying database columns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  A new model or column without a migration is a deployment gap.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Commit all changes** before the verify phase begins. Uncommitted work\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  is flagged as blocking by the verifier.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Stay in scope** — only commit work under this task's ID. Do not bundle\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  changes from adjacent subtasks or refactor unrelated code.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Add indexes on new FK columns** in `__table_args__` when adding\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  foreign key relationships.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Keep CHANGELOG entries consistent** with actual behavior. Do not copy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  descriptions from other tasks or specs without verifying they match\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  the implemented code.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Validation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRun before final commit:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\npip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAll must pass.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Address this recurri