CHANGELOG.md:400:- Added depth-2 groove-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0082): `tests/test_groove_engine.py` now includes `GrooveEngineEndToEndTests`, which drives `groove_for_section(...)`, entrainment tempo nudging, IOI adjustment, meter-policy overlay, JSON-safe groove metadata, and `build_scene_from_score(...)` through one deterministic tracker scene. `tests/test_test_groove_engine_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Production fixes keep entrainment from stripping registered groove shape by replacing the existing immutable profile rather than rebuilding a partial one, and tracker scene compilation now falls back to a resolved profile's lane offsets before using the global default. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4551 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:420:- Added depth-2 functional-harmony end-to-end test coverage (frac-0072): `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` now includes `FunctionalHarmonyEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing harmony public API through live-like keyboard/garden/outdoor/inner inputs, resolved harmonic planning, reharm lookup, modulation continuity checks, score-tree section construction, and JSON-safe round-trip output. The end-to-end scenarios verify meaningful `HarmonicPlan` fields (`G:lydian` keyboard authority, extended palette, pedal-point voicing, scene keys, section functions/cadences/progressions, chord-degree triads, harmonic functions, transition intents, and modulation path), align `reharm_plan_for_song()` / `progression_bank_for_section()` with the resolved plan, assert tension and cadence targets across the arc, and prove `ScoreTree` persistence preserves derived harmonic function and transition intent metadata. `tests/test_test_functional_harmony_depth.py` pins `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function harmony assertions and production `reharmonizer.py`, `harmonic_planner.py`, and `score_tree.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4487 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:448:- Added depth-2 arrangement-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0058): `tests/test_arrangement_engine.py` now includes `TestArrangementEngineEndToEnd`, which drives the existing SenseWeave arrangement public surface through complete tracker-form plans, scene timeline contracts, polyphony variant entry counts, active-voice growth and support dropouts, support thinning while preserving primary continuity, register-band validity, automation interpolation, payoff-scene shaping, cadence quieting/practice lift, JSON-safe dataclass rendering, and multi-family shape compatibility. `tests/test_arrangement_engine_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 25 real functions versus 24 trivial). Existing arrangement-engine assertions and production source behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:494:- Added depth-2 startle daemon processing (frac-0034): `my-claw/tools/startle_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `read_room_activity`, `amp_from_room`, `update_baseline`, `baseline_value`, `render_output`, `write_output`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus a `DaemonState` dataclass that combines the existing `senseweave.startle.StartleState` with a rolling-baseline tracker. The daemon now reads `/tmp/room_activity.json`, takes the louder of `window_mic_amp` / `cypherclaw_mic_amp`, maintains a 20-sample rolling-median baseline (with a non-zero floor so the detector never sees a degenerate baseline), runs the existing `update_startle` rules, and atomically writes the consumer contract (`startled`, `startle_count`, `cooldown_active`, `face_reaction`, `should_mute`, `amp`, `baseline`, `timestamp`) consumed by `inner_life.world_model.poll_state`. Loop control gains `--once`, `--interval`, `--room-path`, `--state-path`, and `--max-iterations`; existing `senseweave.startle` rules are unchanged. `tests/test_startle_daemon.py` pins import safety, baseline/amp helpers, end-to-end loud-room startle output, and quiet-room loop output; `tests/test_startle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:514:- Added depth-2 score-tree report helpers (frac-0024): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py` now exposes frozen `ScoreTreeSectionReport` and `ScoreTreeReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `motif_lifecycle_band`, `section_phrase_load_band`, `count_motif_lifecycle_states`, `build_score_tree_section_report`, `build_score_tree_report`, and `summarize_score_tree_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can resolve a `ScoreTree` into operator-readable shape diagnostics — per-section view (id, scene, function, harmonic role/function, cadence, groove, transition intent, transform strength, target duration, phrase count, named phrase-load band, ordered de-duplicated motif refs across the section's phrases, and a `production_course_complete` flag against `PRODUCTION_COURSE_KEYS`) and tree-level view (piece id, title, form family/class/composition mode, ending family, planned duration, section/motif/phrase counts, ordered `motif_lifecycle_counts` covering every `MOTIF_LIFECYCLE_STATES` entry with zeros for absent states, ordered tuple of unreferenced motif ids, and per-section reports) — and emit a JSON-safe summary mirroring those fields. Existing `MOTIF_LIFECYCLE_STATES`, `PRODUCTION_COURSE_KEYS`, `MotifNode`, `PhraseNode`, `SectionNode`, and `ScoreTree.to_dict` / `to_json` / `from_dict` / `minimal` semantics are preserved so the JSON round-trip and minimal-tree behavior continue unchanged; `tests/test_score_tree_depth.py` pins lifecycle-band mapping (with `"unclassified"` fallback for unknown states), phrase-load band cutpoints, canonical-only lifecycle counting, populated-tree section/tree shape, JSON round-trip stability, minimal-tree zero-state handling, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_score_tree.py` and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` remain regression anchors (the latter for the narrative HTTP `/healthz` + `/readyz` + bearer-token hardening surface).
CHANGELOG.md:526:- Added depth-2 duration contrast report helpers (frac-0018): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/duration_contrast.py` now exposes frozen `LaneDurationContrastStat` and `DurationContrastReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_duration_contrast_stat`, `analyze_duration_contrast`, and `summarize_duration_contrast_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R4 rule once and read back per-lane shaping outcomes (lane name, role, step count, shaped-step count, mean rendered/original length ratio, longest-row and shortest-row indices, and an `applies` flag for role-gated and grid-locked-metadata lanes), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary (totals, lane counts, applied-lane count, per-lane entries) without re-walking the tracker scene tree. Existing `MIN_MULTIPLIER`, `MAX_MULTIPLIER`, `DurationContrastRule.apply`, and `apply_duration_contrast` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_duration_contrast_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_duration_contrast_depth.py` pins per-step length-ratio counting, non-melodic and grid-locked-lane non-application, scene/song aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:530:- Added depth-2 lung capacity report helpers (frac-0016): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/lung_capacity.py` now exposes frozen `LaneBreathStat` and `LungCapacityReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_breath_stat`, `analyze_lung_capacity`, and `summarize_lung_capacity_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R11 rule once and read back per-lane breath outcomes (lane name, voice, role, resolved capacity seconds, inserted vs. tagged breath counts, and an `applies` flag for role-gated wind/voice lanes), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary (totals, lane counts, applied-lane count, per-lane entries) without re-walking the tracker scene tree. Existing `LungCapacityRule.apply`, `apply_lung_capacity`, and `lung_capacity_seconds_for_voice` semantics are preserved so MIDI/Theramini/score-tree callers and `tests/test_lung_capacity_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_lung_capacity_depth.py` pins inserted-vs-tagged counting, non-wind lane non-application, scene/song aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:534:- Added depth-2 production course helpers (frac-0014): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/production_course.py` now exposes frozen `CourseSummary`, `ChapterDigest`, `ArcPhaseSnapshot`, and `CourseArcPlan` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_course`, `chapter_digest`, `catalog_digest`, `arc_phase_snapshot`, `arc_phase_snapshots`, `course_titles`, `plan_course_arc`, and `validate_course` so runtime diagnostics and tests can render an operator-readable view of a section course (chapter count, transition type, mix role, resolved concept titles in declared chapter order), digest each chapter with its first three sample concept values, snapshot every required arc phase with a `sparse` / `balanced` / `dense` density bucket, plan an arc end-to-end by reusing `course_for_section` across a sequence of section descriptors with the last transition cleanly resolving to `terminal`, and report unknown-value chapters as a sorted tuple. Existing `REQUIRED_CHAPTER_IDS`, `REQUIRED_PHASE_NAMES`, `COURSE_CHAPTERS`, `ARC_PHASE_PROFILES`, `load_course_chapters`, `load_arc_phase_profiles`, `course_chapter`, `course_concept`, `arc_phase_profile`, `transition_type_for_section`, and `course_for_section` semantics are preserved so the score-tree composer and `tests/test_production_course_knowledge_base.py` / `tests/test_production_course_integration.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_production_course_depth.py` pins summary title order, chapter digest metadata + `KeyError` on unknown ids, catalog digest coverage, density bucketing + `KeyError` on unknown phase, end-to-end arc plan + empty short-circuit, and validator behavior, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:536:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:544:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:546:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins tracker→world→default fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
CHANGELOG.md:599:- Added the missing CCS-028 sample-usage journal seam for tracker pieces: `senseweave.usage_journal` now serializes the richer per-piece sampler fields (`started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used`, `transformations`, `clicks`) while preserving the legacy `timestamp` / `samples_played` aliases, `music_tracker_runtime.ScheduledTrackerEvent` now carries sample-gesture metadata through playback emission, `duet_composer.py` now records actual emitted sample-lane events into the post-piece journal hook, and new regression coverage in `tests/test_usage_journal.py`, `tests/test_music_tracker_runtime.py`, and `tests/test_usage_journal_integration.py` composes a short score-tree piece end to end and proves the written journal entry contains populated sample usage, transformations, and arc payoff data.
CHANGELOG.md:619:- Added operator diagnostics for production-course decisions: `operator_diagnostics.py` now extracts production-course chapter values (phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile) from tracker runtime `scene_metadata` with fallback to score-tree sections; Theramini relation combines counterpoint relation with live Theramini playing state; critique notes derive threshold violations from ear-engine metrics; all three fields degrade gracefully to "unavailable" when authority files are absent or corrupt; `/status` display renders the new fields in the SenseWeave section.
CHANGELOG.md:621:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
CHANGELOG.md:631:- Implemented ST1-ST6 of the score-tree songwriting stack end to end: added `piece_commission.py`, `piece_brief.py`, `form_grammar.py`, `score_tree.py`, `recursive_composer.py`, `composition_gate.py`, `tracker_compiler.py`, and `piece_queue.py`; extended `repertoire_memory.py` to store structural score-tree summaries; and rewired `duet_composer.py` so tracker solo mode can commission a piece, build a complete score tree, gate it, compile it into tracker scenes, and precompose the next piece into a small persistent queue instead of treating the tracker as the composer.
CHANGELOG.md:632:- Rebalanced the first live score-tree pass for audibility: fresh post-restart commissions now avoid jumping straight to a maximal sparse suite unless the cadence is already wind-down/sleep-oriented, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` now emits stronger safe amplitudes for primary melody/bass/rhythm lanes so a healthy running piece is easier to hear and meter.
CHANGELOG.md:633:- Fixed the long-section tracker compile bug that was turning songs into isolated sustained tones: `tracker_compiler.py` now converts large section budgets into repeat counts plus modest note-length scaling, and `music_tracker.py` quantizes those repeats into real repeated phrase cycles instead of stretching a handful of notes across the whole scene.
CHANGELOG.md:634:- Finished the next score-tree composition pass: `tracker_compiler.py` now derives and enriches a fresh score per section, applies section-function and motif-aware phrase transforms before tracker quantization, and `music_tracker.py` now varies repeated cycles inside long sections, so longer pieces can develop through distinct section writing instead of only looping one shared phrase body.
CHANGELOG.md:635:- Added internal phrase-family development inside longer sections: `Phrase` now carries metadata, `tracker_compiler.py` expands section bodies into recursive families like `A`, `A_prime`, and `B`, and `music_tracker.py` annotates emitted steps with `internal_phrase_family` so development sections can be tested and diagnosed as more than literal loops.
CHANGELOG.md:636:- Coordinated those internal phrase families across tracker roles: shared root/function profiles now shape melody, bass, counter, and color variants together, and tracker steps expose `internal_family_root_degree` plus `internal_family_function` for diagnostics and future orchestration consumers.
CHANGELOG.md:637:- Added authored section transitions: `tracker_compiler.py` now tags each non-final scene with the next scene/function/root target, and `music_tracker.py` marks and retunes final-cycle tail steps as transition preparation so long sections aim into the following section instead of simply looping until a hard boundary.
CHANGELOG.md:638:- Added staged lane windows inside repeated tracker scenes: `music_tracker.py` now assigns per-role `entry_cycle` / `exit_cycle` metadata and delays counter/color support in long development-style sections, so sections can thicken internally instead of launching every lane at row 0.
CHANGELOG.md:640:- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
CHANGELOG.md:641:- Added section-level rhythmic development: `tracker_compiler.py` now maps section functions to named rhythm cells such as steady statement, syncopated fragment, half-time displacement, recall groove, and residue breath, reshaping phrase durations/accents and exposing `rhythm_development` / `rhythm_cell` through tracker metadata.
CHANGELOG.md:643:- Added arrangement automation curves to tracker playback: `music_tracker.py` now derives `arrangement_curve` from section rhythm, writes row-point automation for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, shapes note velocity across each lane's active window, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` / `duet_composer.py` now expose and apply interpolated automation to the live master bus during the section. Low density also thins optional color/counter runtime events while preserving melody and bass continuity.
CHANGELOG.md:645:- Rebalanced the live song mix after the repeat-cycle fix: `music_tracker_runtime.py` now gives texture lanes a stronger floor while slightly easing bass dominance, and `emsd_performance.py` now uses a gentler amp-scaling curve so normal `away_practice` songs no longer pin bass and melody at the top of the EMSD gain range.
CHANGELOG.md:646:- Fixed the live score-tree runtime on CypherClaw: `duet_composer.py` now derives commission context defensively from the world when `TrackerPlan` lacks `day_phase` / `weekly_phase`, `master_bus.py` now exposes an explicit `sw_master_smooth` seed helper, and `restart_composer.sh` now reseeds that master node again after the new composer PID is confirmed alive so the first piece does not run with scene-level `/n_set` traffic targeting a dead node.
CHANGELOG.md:647:- Added a concrete score-tree composition spec for the next songwriting pass: `cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md` now defines the piece commission layer, narrative brief contract, section-function grammar, score-tree data model, recursive composer, composition gate, tracker compiler, repertoire score-tree memory, and rollout phases needed to move CypherClaw from short tracker-first sketches toward longer, more varied composed pieces.
CHANGELOG.md:655:- Locked the EMSD room sampler to tracker transport: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits `transport_trigger_now` / `transport_trigger_key`, `sample_playback_engine.py` uses those keys to launch once per musical bucket instead of only by cooldown, and the face/status layer can now reflect that transport-synchronized sampler execution.
CHANGELOG.md:658:- Added real EMSD master-bus control: `master_bus.py` now translates live `mix_*` fields plus tracker-scene `master_amp` / `reverb_send` automation into `sw_master_smooth` `/n_set` updates at scene start, so EMSD mix intent now shapes the summed output path instead of only per-note rendering.
CHANGELOG.md:659:- Extended hook phrasing into actual later-section pitch behavior: `score_from_mood()` now publishes hook answer-degree metadata, and `music_tracker.py` uses that data in `Recap` / `Release` / `Resolution` / `Afterglow` so later sections can answer harmonically as well as textually.
CHANGELOG.md:683:- Made the sampler musically scene-aware instead of only transform-aware: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits scene profiles like `development_grains`, `theme_accents`, `recap_echo`, `divination_bed`, and `afterglow_residue`, and `sample_event_renderer.py` now changes duration, density, peak target, filtering, stretch, and echo geometry from those profiles so the room layer follows the tracker form instead of using one generic behavior under different labels.
CHANGELOG.md:692:- Fed EMSD production plans into actual tracker playback: added `emsd_performance.py`, wired `duet_composer.py` to apply live mix/sample/DSP adjustments at the note boundary, extended `composer_emsd_extras()` with concrete sample capture metadata, and made the strongest top register fold down harder so notes above roughly `C6` are lowered an octave and the sharpest band is lowered two octaves.
CHANGELOG.md:693:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
CHANGELOG.md:704:- Tightened repertoire hook language and payoff shaping: answer-mode hooks now use phrase-level transforms instead of awkward generic suffixes, repertoire memory can target a preferred payoff scene, and tracker runtime state now exposes scene metadata like `payoff_focus` for live correlation.
CHANGELOG.md:705:- Extended repertoire influence into tracker form memory: the live composer can now inherit a prior strong song's preferred progression profile, title/hook recall mode, form variant, and section-density bias before building the next tracker song.
CHANGELOG.md:707:- Built the first complete M1-M6 musicianship package end to end: added `reharmonizer.py`, `hook_engine.py`, `arrangement_engine.py`, `ear_engine.py`, `practice_curriculum.py`, `prosody_engine.py`, and `repertoire_memory.py`; extended `harmonic_planner.py`, `generative_scores.py`, `music_tracker.py`, `continuous_learner.py`, `duet_composer.py`, and `keyboard_chat.py` so tracker songs now carry section functions, cadence types, hook metadata, scene arrangement intent, practice-block focus, ear-metric evaluation, repertoire storage, and face-visible song titles/captions through the live runtime.
CHANGELOG.md:709:- Lowered the live bass register further, widened per-patch octave spacing across bass/melody/counter/color, and made that register policy survive the whole tracker pipeline by preserving patch metadata through family shaping, cadence clamping, tracker scene building, and runtime scheduling.
CHANGELOG.md:710:- Broke the fixed tracker-song mold: `tracker_form_for_family(..., song_num=...)` now yields variant forms with different scene counts and scene-length multipliers, so CypherClaw no longer plays every song with the same five-scene duration profile.
CHANGELOG.md:712:- Diversified family and harmonic planning across the day and week: `resolve_tracker_plan()` now rotates through day-phase and weekly-phase family palettes instead of pinning occupied daytime songs to one family, and it emits progression profiles like `open_day`, `lift`, `settling`, and `experiment` so the score generator changes chord motion as well as form.
CHANGELOG.md:713:- Added family-level motif memory to the live tracker path: `ContinuousLearner` now tags songs with tracker family, progression profile, cadence state, and patch context, `MelodicMemory` can retrieve matching fragments by keyword, and `score_from_mood()` now prefers and answers same-family/profile motifs instead of drawing only from a generic recent fragment pool.
CHANGELOG.md:714:- Added scene-level tracker recall inside each song: `build_korsakov_tracker_song()` now lets `Recap` and short-form `Release` borrow motif shapes from the already-built `Theme` scene with answering transforms and provenance metadata, so those sections feel like intentional returns instead of parallel re-renderings of the same score.
CHANGELOG.md:716:- Replaced the provisional tracker patch set with named house patches (`house_monastery`, `house_chamber`, `house_garden`, `house_procession`, `house_workshop`) and retired `bell` / `metal` from live runtime playback, so CypherClaw now stays inside a more coherent western-compatible ensemble even when the cast contains those older inharmonic voices.
CHANGELOG.md:717:- Added a motif-driven score generator to `generative_scores.py` and threaded `song_num`, tracker family, cadence state, and recent melodic-memory fragments into live score generation, so CypherClaw can now both invent fresh melody cells and recall transformed motifs instead of rebuilding the same contour-only phrase and comping pattern across similar songs.
CHANGELOG.md:721:- Added a mode-aware harmonic planner and live keyboard-grimoire path: tracker solo now preserves major/minor/modal key specs, ignores stale garden and MIDI files, supports scene-level modulation, and `midi_keyboard_listener.py` discovers the real keyboard devices while publishing pedal-derived harmonic suggestions.
CHANGELOG.md:722:- Widened tracker orchestration so CypherClaw can actually use the broader character-instrument registry: cast planning now keeps a support-role character in low-energy songs, tracker role hints recognize metal/grain/pad/tabla synths, and runtime voice routing preserves those explicit lane instruments instead of collapsing them to legacy fallbacks.
CHANGELOG.md:723:- Tuned tracker voice routing to be lane-aware again after the orchestration widening pass: ringing `metal`/`bell`/`pad` hints are normalized away from long quiet texture/counter lanes, and tracker runtime restores a pad safety fallback so subdued scenes do not sit on a constant unregulated tone.
CHANGELOG.md:724:- Added cadence-aware tracker voice softening for `wind_down` and sleep-adjacent scenes, so chirpy `pluck`/`kotekan`/`grain` cast hints are remapped toward bowed, breath, choir, or gong voices before late-night playback.
CHANGELOG.md:725:- Quarantined tracker `grain` playback to `breath` on the live runtime after discovering hundreds of leaked `sw_grain` nodes building up in scsynth and collapsing the speaker output into broadband static.
CHANGELOG.md:731:- Added canonical `presence_engine.py` and `cadence_engine.py`, wired them into the CypherClaw boot path, taught `world_model.py` to trust `/tmp/presence_state.json` and `/tmp/cadence_state.json`, and made tracker solo clamp tempo inside the published cadence band.
CHANGELOG.md:733:- Made CypherClaw tracker solo cast-aware: the live composer now derives tracker lane voice hints from the active character cast and enforces a quiet foundation lane through subdued `Theme`/`Development`/`Recap` scenes.
docs/architecture.md:282:CypherClaw's tracker orchestration now also has an explicit instrument-patch layer. Cast voices are no longer used as a flat pool during normal listening: songs resolve into named house patches such as `house_monastery`, `house_chamber`, `house_garden`, `house_procession`, and `house_workshop`, with normal occupied listening biased toward `bowed`, `pluck`, `choir`, and `breath`. Those house patches are now musical as well as timbral: each patch carries its own contour bias, bass/comping vocabulary, dynamic envelope, and wider register spread. The older `bell` and `metal` voices are retired from live playback and degraded to tuned substitutes at runtime.
docs/architecture.md:283:That patch layer now reaches all the way through tracker runtime and playback too: patch metadata survives family shaping and cadence clamping, live tracker scenes apply per-patch octave floors and ceilings by role, tracker forms vary by song number instead of always using one fixed five-scene length, and very high notes are softened with a small saturation-style shaping pass because the live synth surface does not expose a dedicated drive control.
docs/architecture.md:284:Family planning is now more authored as well. `resolve_tracker_plan()` no longer pins large parts of the day to one family like `bloom`; it rotates through day-phase and weekly-phase family palettes, while also emitting a harmonic progression profile such as `awakening`, `open_day`, `lift`, `settling`, or `experiment` so the score generator changes not just scene shape but harmonic material across the day.
docs/architecture.md:288:The live CypherClaw solo music scheduler is also now tracker-first: it selects an active character cast, maps those character roles into tracker lane voice hints, and applies scene-level role floors so subdued moods still keep a cast-grounded foundation lane through `Theme`, `Development`, and `Recap`.
docs/architecture.md:289:That tracker path is now also mode-aware. Harmonic authority flows through the keyboard grimoire and the new harmonic planner: fresh keyboard, inner-life, and garden hints are normalized into a canonical key spec, scene-level modulation is planned before tracker scheduling, and stale outdoor or MIDI state is ignored instead of pinning the whole piece to an old major root.
docs/architecture.md:290:Melodic authority is now song-aware too. `score_from_mood()` seeds a motif-driven generator with song number, tracker family, cadence state, and recent melodic-memory fragments so repeated moods can still yield different note cells, rhythm cells, leap profiles, and occasional recalled motifs instead of recycling one default contour under new keys. The same generator now rotates comping styles as well, so the foundation line does not keep repeating one root-walk pattern.
docs/architecture.md:291:That motif system now has family memory instead of only recency memory. The live learner tags each tracker song with family, progression profile, cadence state, and house patch, recent in-session fragments can be recalled by matching those tags, and persisted melodic memory can rank stored fragments by the same keywords so re-entering `ember` or `drift` can produce an answer or recall gesture from earlier related songs instead of sounding fully disconnected.
docs/architecture.md:292:That recall now also happens inside a single tracker song. Once `Theme` exists, later scenes such as `Recap` and short-form `Release` can explicitly borrow lane-level motif shapes from it, rescale them to the new scene length, and resolve them with a small answering transform. That gives the form an actual memory curve instead of making every scene a fresh quantization of the same phrase-level score.
docs/architecture.md:293:The next musicianship layer is now live as a real end-to-end stack rather than only a roadmap. M1 adds a reharmonization layer through `reharmonizer.py` and `harmonic_planner.py`, so tracker songs carry section functions, cadence types, and a named reharm strategy. M2 adds a hook engine through `hook_engine.py`, which now emits deterministic song-title, hook-text, hook-type, and phrase-pair material that survives into score metadata. M3 adds `arrangement_engine.py`, which turns tracker forms into section-level groove and automation plans instead of treating every scene as a raw template replay. M4 adds `ear_engine.py` plus deliberate `practice_curriculum.py` blocks, so performed notes are analyzed for interval variety, hook clarity, leap ratio, register spread, and cadence strength while away-mode songs can focus on Harmony, Melody, Arrangement, Ear, or Scene labs. M5 adds `prosody_engine.py`, which gives tracker songs short titles and scene captions that the face layer can surface. M6 adds `repertoire_memory.py`, a long-term song memory that stores titles, hook text, cadence/family context, and ear metrics so CypherClaw can gradually accumulate a repertoire instead of living only in fragment memory.
docs/architecture.md:294:That M1-M6 layer is now threaded through the live tracker path. `duet_composer.py` selects a practice block, resolves harmonic section metadata, writes title/hook/prosody state into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, stores completed songs into repertoire memory, and lets the face surface a song title and scene caption instead of only key and movement changes. The result is a more authored pipeline: function and cadence inform the form, the score now has a named hook, the tracker carries section intent, the learner judges the result, and the piece can remember whole songs as well as motifs.
docs/architecture.md:295:The next songwriting layer is now active above that tracker runtime too. CypherClaw no longer has to treat the tracker as the composer: `piece_commission.py` chooses a form class, composition mode, duration target, groove identity, and ending family; `piece_brief.py` turns world/narrative state into a concrete brief; `form_grammar.py` expands that into section functions with duration budgets; `recursive_composer.py` turns the brief plus hook profile into a full `ScoreTree`; `composition_gate.py` rejects underbuilt sketches; and `tracker_compiler.py` compiles approved trees into tracker scenes only after the whole-piece architecture exists. `piece_queue.py` keeps a small queue of precomposed score trees at `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/state/piece_queue.json`, so the live runtime can keep one committed piece active while preparing the next one in the background instead of improvising every song from scratch. `repertoire_memory.py` now stores a `score_tree_summary` alongside the old surface metadata, which means repertoire can remember section functions, motif ids, narrative beats, and ending family rather than only titles and hook text. The live commission layer now also carries an audibility bias: the very first post-boot piece is capped away from maximal suite scale unless the cadence is already in sleep or wind-down territory, so runtime recovery produces a committed audible piece instead of immediately disappearing into a sparse ten-minute introduction. And long section budgets now expand mostly through repeated phrase cycles rather than by stretching every note into a drone, which keeps long-form pieces song-like when they are compiled down into tracker rows. That compiler layer is now section-aware too: each scene gets its own derived score, section-function transforms, and motif-aware rewrites before quantization, so `Theme`, `Development`, `Recap`, and `Afterglow` no longer share one base phrase body with only density changes on top. Longer scenes now also carry coordinated internal phrase families such as `A`, `A_prime`, and `B` inside the same section body, with tracker-step root/function provenance, so a development section can unfold recursively while melody, bass, counter, and color lanes follow the same harmonic turns before any repeat-cycle variation is applied. Scene endings are now transition-aware as well: non-final sections know the next section's target function and root, and the tracker reshapes only the final repeat cycle's tail events into preparation tones so section boundaries behave like composed handoffs rather than hard resets. `recursive_composer.py` also now runs a metadata-only meter trajectory planner while building the tree: ordered per-scene values such as `4/4`, `15/16`, and `7/8` are chosen from the arc-phase drift table, round-trip through `MeterTrajectory`, and survive compilation into tracker scene metadata before later runtime slices make them active. Each emitted scene also carries a JSON `meter_trajectory_entry` for its planned meter value, and generic tracker scene emission can derive those per-scene keys from the compact trajectory payload.
docs/architecture.md:296:The tracker quantizer also now has a simple arrangement timeline inside repeated scenes. It computes per-role `entry_cycle` / `exit_cycle` windows, so support lanes can arrive after the foundation and melody in `Development`, `Bridge`, or `Lift` sections. This is deliberately separate from note variation: the same phrase family can exist, but the ensemble density changes over time.
docs/architecture.md:298:The compiler now adds a section-local motif/progression layer above those tracker mechanics. `tracker_compiler.py` derives a named motif-development mode from each section function, rewrites melody/counter material accordingly, chooses a local four-step harmonic progression from the section's harmonic role/function, and reshapes bass/counter/color/melody notes against that progression. The tracker then preserves `motif_development`, `section_progression`, and per-step progression roots/roles, which makes a long piece more like related thematic development than one motif poured through unrelated scene templates.
docs/architecture.md:299:The same compiler layer now owns section rhythm identity. `tracker_compiler.py` maps section functions onto named rhythm-development modes and duration cells, then rewrites phrase durations and accents before internal phrase-family expansion. That means `Development` can be recognizably syncopated, `Bridge` can feel displaced or half-time, `Arrival` can drive, and `Afterglow` can breathe out while all of those choices remain inspectable through tracker metadata.
docs/architecture.md:301:The tracker now turns that section identity into audible arrangement curves. `music_tracker.py` maps `rhythm_development` into an `arrangement_curve`, writes multi-point automation lanes for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, and shapes each lane's note velocity across its own active window without raising the register. `music_tracker_runtime.py` publishes interpolated row automation in `/tmp/tracker_runtime_state.json`, uses low density to thin optional color/counter events while preserving bass and melody, and `duet_composer.py` periodically applies those current values to `sw_master_smooth`, so a long `Development` can actually rise, a `Bridge` can open into suspended reverb, and residues can fade instead of looping at one flat mix level.
docs/architecture.md:303:That EMSD layer is now live in the tracker path too. Before each tracker song is built, `duet_composer.py` constructs an EMSD context from cadence state, occupancy, family, patch, attention, CPU pressure, Theramini presence, and repertoire history. That context can now bias the active density shape, and its arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields are written into `/tmp/composer_state.json` at scene boundaries. `self_listener.py` also reads those fields back alongside `/tmp/cadence_state.json` and publishes `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json`, so GlyphWeave-facing consumers can finally see brightness, motion, density, sample source, DSP blocks, and arc phase as a coherent audio-driven surface rather than inferring them from raw transport state. When direct self-capture hangs on the live JACK recorder path, that listener can now fall back to a fresh `/tmp/room_capture.wav` clip instead of dropping all the way to a dark `capture_timeout` state.
docs/architecture.md:310:That restart path now also reseeds the `sw_master_smooth` node twice on purpose: once while the outputs are muted and the old composer is down, and again after the new `duet_composer.py` process is confirmed alive. The second reseed matters because the composer clears the root group on startup before building the next piece, which would otherwise leave scene-level master-bus automation writing to a dead node and make the runtime effectively silent even while tracker events are still being scheduled.
docs/architecture.md:314:The operator diagnostics path now reads those same authority files through `my-claw/tools/senseweave/operator_diagnostics.py` and renders them in daemon `/status`. That keeps status output aligned with the live score-tree, tracker, composer, sampler, master-bus, and self-listener contracts instead of showing only daemon counters. SenseWeave behavior gates live in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/rollout_controls.py` and are controlled by `CYPHERCLAW_ENABLE_CURRICULUM_EXERCISE`, `CYPHERCLAW_ENABLE_PREVIEW_RENDER`, `CYPHERCLAW_ENABLE_SELF_CRITIQUE`, and `CYPHERCLAW_ENABLE_LONG_FORM_SUITE`, so curriculum exercises, preview metrics, revision passes, and suite-scale commissioning can be rolled back independently.
docs/architecture.md:318:The sampler plan itself is now scene-aware and transport-aware too. `sample_dsp_activity.py` no longer chooses only a generic mode from transforms and DSP blocks; it also reads the 30-minute arc phase plus tracker scene and row state from the self-listener, then emits a scene profile such as `development_grains`, `theme_accents`, `recap_echo`, `divination_bed`, or `afterglow_residue` together with a transport trigger key. `sample_event_renderer.py` consumes that profile to change grain count, event duration, bed spacing, echo spacing, peak target, filter ceiling, and stretch, and `sample_playback_engine.py` now uses the transport key to launch once per musical bucket instead of free-running only on cooldown. The practical effect is that `Development` room material can widen into denser grain clouds while `Afterglow` and `Resolution` can leave a longer, softer residue instead of sharing the same generic freeze or slice pattern.
docs/architecture.md:320:That repertoire layer is no longer passive. Before each tracker song is built, the live composer now asks `repertoire_memory.py` for an influence object keyed by family and cadence state. That influence can bias the next song's progression profile as well as title and hook generation, and it can now also recommend a tracker form variant, a section-density bias, and a preferred payoff scene. Strong earlier songs can therefore echo forward not only as language and harmony, but also as structural memory that nudges the next song toward bridge, concise, or afterglow forms with a matching density contour and a remembered place of arrival. The hook path now also uses phrase-level answer transforms instead of a blunt suffix fallback, and those transforms are context-aware rather than single-template replacements: the same recalled hook can answer differently across family, cadence, and song context while staying grammatical. The hook generator now normalizes a small set of historically awkward phrases too, so rough forms like `carry the line wide` or `open the room open` collapse back into musically usable hooks before they can propagate through repertoire recall. Title generation is now tied to the same image field as the hook at the phrase level, not just the noun level, and that title planner now also reacts to cadence state, progression profile, and hook type. The result is that calmer hooks can land in phrases like `Low Light` or `Quiet Rooms`, while brighter or more kinetic hooks can move toward `Electric Circuits`, `Moving Lines`, or `Open Thresholds` instead of repeating one adjective-noun template. The same planner also avoids exact title repeats from remembered repertoire hints, so callback titles can echo earlier songs without cloning them verbatim. The prosody layer now reshapes that same hook by section too, so `Theme`, `Recap`, `Release`, `Resolution`, and `Afterglow` can carry the same motif with different textual density instead of reusing one caption verbatim across the whole song. That caption shaping is now harmonic-function-aware as well: the same `Afterglow` hook can read differently under `half`, `plagal`, `authentic`, or `deceptive` cadences, which lets the face text follow the actual harmonic landing rather than only the scene name. It is now orchestration-aware too: sparse `house_monastery` or `house_chamber` scenes can compress a hook into a leaner noun phrase, while denser `house_workshop` or `house_procession` scenes can widen the same hook into a fuller line, which lets the face react to texture before the harmony resolves. `repertoire_memory.py` also repairs legacy broken hook text on load and on write, so older bad phrases do not keep leaking forward into new songs after the hook system improves.
docs/architecture.md:323:The tracker orchestration path now also preserves a wider instrument palette, but with lane-aware and cadence-aware safety. Cast planning keeps at least one non-core support role on stage even during lower-energy songs, direct character synths can pass through the tracker runtime when they match the lane semantics, and quiet `wind_down` or sleep scenes automatically soften chirpy `pluck`/`kotekan`/`grain` choices toward bowed, breath, choir, or gong voices so the late-night organism does not sound like daytime birds. `sw_grain` is also quarantined at tracker runtime for now because the live SynthDef was leaking nodes and accumulating into broadband static overnight, and the runtime aliases `tabla_ge` to `tabla_tin` until a real `sw_tabla_ge` SynthDef exists in the deployed bundle. Primary tracker-role gains are now deliberately hotter too: bass, melody, and rhythm lanes carry a higher live floor than the earlier sketch-era defaults so a valid running piece cannot hide under the room noise floor merely because the new score-tree layer chose a restrained opening. That role floor is now balanced rather than just louder: bass no longer dominates by default, texture lanes carry a meaningful minimum presence, and EMSD note-level mix shaping no longer hard-clamps normal daytime bass/melody material at the top of its amp range.

